---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import bearRoar from "/images/bear-roar-art.webp";
import bearWalk1 from "/images/bear-sketch-walk.webp";
import bearWalk2 from "/images/bear-sketch-walk2.webp";
import bearWalk3 from "/images/bear-sketch-walk3.webp";
import bearWalk4 from "/images/bear-sketch-walk4.webp";
---

<Layout 
  title="How to Sketch a Bear Step by Step Drawing Tutorial for Artists" 
  description="Learn how to draw a bear with step-by-step anatomy and rendering tips. Wildlife sketching guide for beginner artists."
>
  <main class="prose mx-auto my-10 text-center">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">How to Sketch a Bear</h1>

    <p class="mb-6">
      Rendering a bear can be challenging for both beginners and advanced artists...
    </p>

    <figure class="mx-auto my-16 text-center">
      <Image
        src={bearRoar}
        alt="Grizzly Bear Roaring Portrait, titled Anger Management"
        widths={[400, 800, 1200]}
        sizes="(max-width: 600px) 400px, 800px"
        loading="lazy"
        class="rounded-xl shadow-lg mx-auto"
      />
      <figcaption class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-zinc-400">
        Bear Roaring Portrait – “Anger Management”
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-10">Step 1: Start with Simple Shapes</h2>
    <p>...</p>

    <figure class="mx-auto my-8 text-center">
      <Image src={bearWalk1} alt="Bear walking sketch on paper" widths={[400,800,1200]} loading="lazy" class="rounded-xl shadow-lg mx-auto" />
      <figcaption class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-zinc-400">Bear walking sketch on paper</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-10">Step 2: Define the Bear’s Anatomy</h2>
    <p>...</p>

    <figure class="mx-auto my-8 text-center">
      <Image src={bearWalk2} alt="Bear sketch structure outlines" widths={[400,800,1200]} loading="lazy" class="rounded-xl shadow-lg mx-auto" />
      <figcaption class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-zinc-400">Bear sketch basic structure outlines</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-10">Step 3: Add Fur and Details</h2>
    <p>...</p>

    <Image src={bearWalk3} alt="Bear sketch fur details" widths={[400,800,1200]} loading="lazy" class="rounded-xl shadow-lg mx-auto" />

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-10">Step 4: Refine and Shade</h2>
    <p>...</p>

    <Image src={bearWalk4} alt="Completed bear sketch shaded" widths={[400,800,1200]} loading="lazy" class="rounded-xl shadow-lg mx-auto" />

    <!-- 🎥 Vimeo video -->
    <div class="my-12 flex justify-center">
      <div class="w-full max-w-2xl aspect-[16/9]">
        <iframe
          src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1116494093?h=ip&fe=ec&muted=1"
          title="Anger Management – Bear Portrait Time-Lapse"
          frameborder="0"
          allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture"
          allowfullscreen
          class="w-full h-full rounded-2xl shadow-lg"
        ></iframe>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-10">Conclusion</h2>
    <p>Learning how to sketch a bear trains your eye for anatomy, rhythm, and texture...</p>
  </main>
</Layout>

